description:
SPINE (locked with architect)
Collapse the two-layer revision model and ~7 hand-rolled reconcile patterns onto ONE trait. Each fact's VALUE type implements:

  trait Reconcile: Sized {
      // None = not-yet-computed (distinct from any value; fixpoint correctness).
      // revision is an opaque 64-bit the fact mints: revision+1, a content hash,
      // or unchanged. The value NEVER stores the revision; the fact system holds
      // and threads it. reconcile did the comparison, so it emits the revision
      // directly (no double-compare -- the quoted walk is the expensive thing).
      fn reconcile(current: Option<&Self>, incoming: Self, revision: u64) -> (Self, u64);
  }

Fact system: let (value, rev) = T::reconcile(store.get(key), incoming, fact.rev(key)); store.put(key, value); if rev != old { propagate }. Change == rev != prior. Fact owns the 64-bit MEANING; system owns STORAGE + PROPAGATION.

WHY (measured + grokked)
- Downstream change-detection already reads the FACT revision (artifact.rs:1830), never the slot revision -> the per-slot revision is a redundant intermediary.
- Value stores are single-authority (one owner per key; FunctionDefined multi-writers target disjoint instances) -> the contributions/join/Presence(u64) multi-contributor layer is vestigial and retires.
- The quoted-source fingerprint eagerly canonical-serializes+hashes every parse (O(n*depth), retained, ~27% of IndexCode) only to feed a digest compare. reconcile replaces it with a lazy fast-fail horizon walk.
- replace_if_changed FUSES store+bump (if changed { store AND bump }) -> the code.index trap: surface-same discards freshly-parsed bodies => stale function facts. Separating value from revision-advance dissolves it by construction.

THREE reconcile behaviors, one interface:
- mechanical (~12 facts: Dispatch/Projection/Body/TypeDef/Protocol x3/CallSite/Contract/FunctionFact): (incoming, revision + (current != Some(incoming)) as u64). Blanket over PartialEq.
- horizon (Code/Module = surface walk skipping do: bodies; Function/FunctionSource = full walk): value always fresh source; revision advances iff the scoped walk differs. Kills fingerprint + key() over-invalidation.
- lattice (Activation return = widen; SemanticClosure = composite): (join(current, incoming), advance iff moved).

Content-hash-as-revision becomes an OPT-IN per fact (the fingerprint's one good idea: same content => same id, order-independent) instead of an eager mandate.

CHILD TICKETS (dependency-ordered) created separately.
